import React from 'react' import { useState } from 'react' import productImage from '../images/carry.png' import hoodieOne from '../images/hoodie1.jpg' import hoodieTwo from '../images/hoodie2.jpg' import teeOne from '../images/tee1.jpg' import teeTwo from '../images/tee2.jpg' import Tilt from 'react-vanilla-tilt' import Ethos from './Ethos' import Parallax from 'react-rellax' const Shop = () => { const [products] = useState([ { title: "CAMO HOODIE", tag: "Camo Hoodie", price: 90, img: hoodieOne, id: 1, quantity: 1 }, { title: "PRIDE HOODIE", tag: "Pride Hoodie", price: 80, img: hoodieTwo, id: 2, quantity: 1 }, { title: "CC TEE", tag: "CC Tee", price: 32, img: teeOne, id: 3, quantity: 1 }, { title: "KLEPTO TEE", tag: "Klepto Tee", price: 32, img: teeTwo, id: 4, quantity: 1 }, ]) return (

HOODIES & TEES

{products.map(product => (

{product.title}

$ {product.price} USD
))}
) } export default Shop
